item.title: Need help
item.dc:creator: @teh_spede Teh Spede
item.description:
@teh_spede wrote:

Download aryan 377 updated by bruteork from this link:http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,2441.0.html then “unzip” it from rar (you need winrar). Then you have to have java (duhuu) and then you have to push the “run bot.bat” file. Then there pops a black window that lists all the scripts (that you use to macro) and all anti-randoms (the things that do the randoms for you). Then there pops an other window that is the client to runescape. Log in (With a macro guy i guess). Then you push the file button that is in the left, up corner. There should be a button that says run. So this is the part where you start the actual script. Now look from the black window (this is called the console). Look at the scripts. Under every script there is an alias (or thats what i like to call 'em). It should be something like this: * /script(). So you should put the alias without the * thing (so like this if you didn’t figure it out: /script() ) in the window that popped when you pushed the run button. So this should start the script. Sometimes like in some autowalkers you have to put like this: /walk(falador, draynor) mpw this means it goes from falador to draynor.

I hope this helped.
